# ~/.config/git/ignore (macOS)
#
#   Global gitignore file.
#
#   Herein are a set of patterns which git automatically
#   excludes from tracking in all repositories by default.
#   These patterns can be explicitly overrided for local
#   by its own local configs and/or .gitignore files.
#
#   Similar to how & where git searches for the user's
#   global gitconfig file, the path ~/.config/git/ignore
#   is seen as an alternative location to ~/.gitconfig (in
#   recent versions of git, apparently).
#
#   Therefore, in theory, when keeping the global config
#   file's (~/.gitconfig OR ~/.config/git/config) core
#   `excludesFile` option empty, git will automatically
#   find and fallback to this ignore file globally.
#
#   Neel Yadav
#   07.07.2021


